#16405
ghost yavathol~
The Ghost of Yavathol~
A watery ghost is here, patiently instructing new mages to take no abuses.
~
You gaze upon a tall ghost built not of ethereal
matter, but of water vapor.  The ghost of Yavathol
wanders about the area offering young mages a gentle
word or two about diplomacy, temperance, patience, and
perserverance.  The ghost of Yavathol also stresses
the importance of guiding and guarding young mages. 
As you look upon the misty ghost, you notice that his
eyes are composed entirely of dark pools of water. 
His gaze turns to settle on you, his slight stare is
somehow both soothing and unnerving.
~
